	<issue id="DE-49" type="general" linkend="" status="closed" category="minor_technical" by="DE-49" date="2004-09-21" seds="no" ballot="PLCS DIS ballot" ballot_comment="yes" ballot_comment_id="DE-49" member_body="GE" resolution="accept">
		<issue_management owner="Sean Barker" priority="low" category="location"/>
		<description>
			<p>
				<b>SC4 part number:</b>
			</p>
			<p>
				<b>(2) Clause:</b> 
				10303-1276
			 </p>
			<p>
				<b>(3) Paragraph:</b> 
				4.3.1
			 </p>
			<p>
				<b>(5) Comment:</b>
			</p>
			<p>
				Entity address_based_location_representation. It is not understandable why the postale-address is of type address_assignment which requires a person or organization. There are cases when we simply want to specify a house or real_estate only by its address not knowing about a specific person or organization at this address; e.g. for maintenance of the water meter in a multi flat house.
			</p>
			<p>
				<b>(6) Proposal:</b>
			</p>
			<p>
				Remove entity address_based_location_representation and extend instead select 4.2.2.location_representation by address and address_assignment.</p>
		</description>
		<comment by="Mike" date="2004-10-22">
			<description>The comment is fully accepted, but the proposal has been modified: The location_representation select type should be replaced with an equivalent abstract supertype.  Once this has been done it is important to retain the Address_based_location_representation entity as a way of inheriting characterizations of the supertype.  It is, however, agreed that Address_based_location_representation should reference Address.  It would be better if Address_assignment were not referenced a all and this should be deleted.  The Module has been amended in accordance with these considerations.</description>
		</comment>
	</issue>
